      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This property controls the automatic window animation behavior used when the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nswindow/1419495-orderfront"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " or "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nswindow/1419660-orderout"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " methods are called. See "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nswindowanimationbehavior"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " for the possible values of this property."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "By default, a window’s animation behavior is set to "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nswindowanimationbehavior/nswindowanimationbehaviordefault"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", which causes AppKit to determine the style of animation to use automatically based on its inference of a window’s “type” from various window properties. A window’s animation behavior can be set to "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nswindowanimationbehavior/nswindowanimationbehaviornone"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to disable AppKit’s automatic animations for the window, which may be useful if that animation interferes with an animation that your application implements."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The animation behavior can also be set to one of the other non-default "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nswindowanimationbehavior"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " values to override AppKit's automatic inference of appropriate animation behavior based on the window's apparent type, although this is not recommended."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
